<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 19 Injured in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Deputy Commandant of
Border Security Force (BSF), his wife, three soldiers and 14
others were injured in an attack by militants while nine people,
including seven militants, were killed in Jammu and Kashmir since
Saturday evening, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
An improvised explosive device fitted on a bicycle was
detonated by militants while BSF Deputy Commandant Harpreet Singh,
with his wife, was returning to his official residence here Sunday
from Soura, they said.
</P>
<P>
The blast took place at a village in Idgah on Soura-Nawakadal
road Sunday evening, according to the Press Trust of India. The
officer's vehicle was also damaged in the explosion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
