<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympic Ticket Sales Set Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The tickets sales of the
Sydney Olympic has set a new record, surpassing Barcelona's mark
of selling a greater percentage of tickets than any other host
city.
</P>
<P>
More than 85 percent of Sydney's tickets have now been sold,
compared with the 82.3 percent sold by Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
People waited in line for up to three hours at box offices
Sunday as 65,000 tickets worth about 2.75 million US dlrs were
sold. Tempers flared when many potential purchasers found that
tickets to several events were not available.
</P>
<P>
More than 5.5 million tickets to events in Sydney and nearly
650,000 to soccer matches in Canberra, Melbourne, Adelaide and
Brisbane have been sold. There are still about 1 million tickets
on offer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
