<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telecom Egypt to Be Offered October: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Information Minister
Safwat el-Sherif said on Monday that the initial public offering of
Telecom Egypt will be made at the end of October.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 percent of the shares of the national
telecommunications firm will be offered on Egyptian and world stock
markets as agreed by the cabinet, el-Sherif was quoted as saying by
the official Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The initial public offered, originally set for June and then
delayed, is expected to bring Egypt between 1.2 and 1.4 billion U.
S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian cabinet agreed on Monday that 10 percent of the
company's shares will be floated on the Egyptian bourse and another
10 percent on world markets, he added, without specifying.
</P>
<P>
Telecom Egypt currently has a monopoly over fixed local and
international lines, and two private companies, namely MobiNil and
Click, are competing in the mobile telephone market. But el-Sherif
said the cabinet has agreed that Telecom Egypt would start offering
mobile phone service from December 2002.
</P>
<P>
Telecom's assets are estimated at between 17 billion Egyptian
pounds (about 4.9 billion dollars) and 19.5 billion pounds (5.6
billion dollars), according to independent evaluations.
</P>
<P>
Economy Minister Yussef Boutros Ghali said earlier this year
that the company was growing at 20 percent a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
