<HEADLINE> EU Grants Zambia 109.6 Million Euros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) Monday
signed an agreement here with the Zambian government, granting the
country 109.6 million euros (93.2 million U.S. dollars) in aid.
</P>
<P>
This is the EU's largest single aid grant ever made to Zambia,
and also one of the largest by the EU ever offered to any country
in African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) region.
</P>
<P>
The grant is to be disbursed to the country between November
this year and December of 2001. It is to be used to support
Zambia's domestic budget management and debt reduction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
