<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Ends Visit to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Monday, the Chinese foreign minister held talks with Cuban
Vice President Carlos Lage, with whom he coincided to underscore
the good level of bilateral historical relations and the
possibilities to increase cooperation in different sectors.
</P>
<P>
Tang also paid tribute to the monument of the national hero of
Cuba, Jose Marti in the Revolution Square at the capital, and
attended a meeting with the diplomatic corps at the headquarters
of the Foreign Department.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan met with
President Castro last Saturday in a friendly and fraternal
atmosphere.
</P>
