<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Links with Rocket Attack in Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Ministry on
Monday rejected Iraqi allegations that Iran had involved in the
rocket attack in Baghdad on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Iran has no links with such activities and Tehran has nothing
to do with Iraq's internal conflicts," an unnamed Foreign Ministry
official said, quoted by the official IRNA news agency.
</P>
<P>
Three 122 mm rockets exploded at residential districts in
Baghdad Sunday morning, injuring one person and destroying several
houses.
</P>
<P>
Iraq accused Iranian agents of being responsible for the attack,
warning that "the crime would not pass without revenge."
</P>
<P>
Iran and Iraq, who fought a bloody war between 1980 and 1988,
are still divided on a range of issues. One of the thorniest issues
is the two countries' support of each other's opposition groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
