<HEADLINE> UK R&AMP;D Spending Decline Threatens Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Substantial increases in
funding for the UK defense and aerospace research programs are
essential or it will lose jobs, a government taskforce has warned.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Department of Trade and Industry calls on the
government to reverse the long run decline in R&AMP;D budgets for
defense and civil aerospace.
</P>
<P>
The report also recommends scrapping the 50:50 rule whereby the
government will only provide funds for R&AMP;D projects provided it is
matched by upfront investment from industry.
</P>
<P>
The official report compiled by the Foresight Directorate's
defense, aerospace and systems panel says that it is of "
significant concern" that support from the UK government for the
defense and aerospace industries has continued to decline on a
yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The panel says it is a "regrettable fact" that UK R&AMP;D funding
fell by some 35 percent in real terms between 1976 and 1996 while
in Europe the budget spend by NATO nations on defense research is
10 billion US dollars compared with 36 billion US dollars in the
US.
</P>
<P>
In the view of the Foresight Panel, the UK needs to
reinvigorate its research base if future competitiveness is to be
assured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
