<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chief of Shell Oil Group Opposes High Oil Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an interview with the daily Le Monde, Moody-Stuart, said
that the "wishable" price of oil should stand at 20 dollars a
barrel, while it attained 36 dollars last Friday in London.
</P>
<P>
He said that everybody has been affected negatively by the
recent rise of oil price, including oil producing countries and
oil companies.
</P>
<P>
"A too high price is bad news for everybody -- The producers,
because that lays stress on the demand for their production and
stimulates substitution energies. The consuming countries whose
tax policies are disputed. Developing countries, whose economies
are affected when fuel prices rise. And oil companies because it
is never good to have unhappy customers," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that although he hopes the oil price can stand at "a
little lower than 20 dollars" a barrel, it is not up to oil
companies alone to decide the price.
</P>
<P>
"We are in a market where two forces oppose each other. On the
one side, the technological advances realized by oil companies to
exploit at low costs new oilfields are pulling the prices down...
On the other side, the OPEC intends to maintain the price at a
high level by regulating its production," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
