<HEADLINE> France Concerned With Kuwait's Security, Stability: French Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior French military
commander said here Monday that France is concerned with Kuwait's
security and stability, hinting that Paris will protect Kuwait from
possible foreign attacks.
</P>
<P>
Herve Giraud, Commander of the French naval forces in the Indian
Ocean, said,"Kuwait's security is France's security," adding his
country is ready to interfere if Kuwait is attacked by any foreign
side.
</P>
<P>
Giraud, who was appointed to the post last August and arrived
here Saturday on a four-day visit, reasserted France is committed
to the joint French-Kuwaiti security agreement, the official Kuwait
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait signed a defense accord with France in 1992, one year
after a multi-national force, including the French troops, freed
Kuwait from the seven-month Iraqi occupation.
</P>
<P>
The French commander said he has come to "express France's
priorities towards the security and stability of the Gulf and
Kuwait."
</P>
<P>
Giraud also expressed happiness with Kuwait for the purchase of
eight French warships, a matter he thought would "make France hold
a special responsibility towards Kuwait."
</P>
<P>
Kuwait signed a deal worth 475 million U.S. dollars in 1995 to
buy the French gunboats facilitated with high-tech fighting
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of four ships was delivered last year, and the
rest four boats are on their way home and will joint the Kuwaiti
navy next October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
