<HEADLINE> MILF Rebels Killed in S. Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Army troops gunned
down 10 Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels in a running
gunbattle Monday morning in the southern Cotabato Province,
military authorities said in a report.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the rebels were killed in a clash
between elements of the Philippine Army's 40th Infantry Battalion
at about 4:30 a.m. in Panicupan, Pikit, Cotabato.
</P>
<P>
The figure of MILF casualties was based on an actual body count
at the scene of the encounter while there were no casualties on
the government side.
</P>
<P>
The report said about 120 MILF guerrillas were about to harass
a military detachment in Panicupan village when alert soldiers
managed to open fire first at the attackers.
</P>
<P>
Recovered from the slain rebels were seven assorted rifles
while most of those killed were teenagers.
</P>
<P>
The 15,000-strong MILF is the Philippines' largest rebel group
which has been fighting for an independent Muslim state in
Mindanao for more than two decades. 
</P>
