<HEADLINE> 23 Militants Killed in Jammu, Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- At least 23 militants were
among the 28 people killed in Jammu and Kashmir even as militants
stepped up attacks on security personnel in the valley, an Indian
Army spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Twelve militants were killed in a fierce encounter with troops
in Mangana forests of the Poonch sector near the Line of Control,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani troops supported the militants by resorting to heavy
shelling from across the border, killing two civilians.
</P>
<P>
Security forces also killed 11 other militants in Poorch,
Udhampur, Doda and other districts.
</P>
