<HEADLINE> Peace Agreement Takes Burundi Forward to Democracy: Presidents  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni and his Burundian counterpart Pierre Buyoya said Monday
that signing of the Burundi Peace and Reconciliation Agreement has
taken the country a step forward towards the establishment of
democratic governance.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders called upon those Burundi parties which have
not yet signed the agreement to do so without any further delay so
that the implementation stage can start, said a press statement
released after the two presidents held talks at the Ugandan city
Entebbe.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the two presidents held extensive
discussions on the current situation in Burundi and on the
progress of the peace negotiations, and also underscored the
importance of a cease-fire for the successful implementation of
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Buyoya arrived in Entebbe this morning for a one-day working
visit to Uganda at the invitation of President Museveni. 
