<HEADLINE> Top CPC Official Stresses Grass-Root Procuratorate Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), today urged
related officials to do better procuratorate work at the grass-
roots level.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, made this remark at a national working meeting on
promoting grass-roots level procuratorate work which opened today
and was presided over by Han Zhubin, procurator-general of the
Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
"As an important law-executing body, procuratorates at all
levels should on one hand carefully observe the law, and on the
other hand enhance their supervisory power so as to guarantee the
justice and sanctity of the law," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Wei, although progress has been made in the last
two years, some problems still need to be solved especially at the
grass-roots level.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that the country's local procuratorates are still
not so satisfactory -- the overall quality of staff is relatively
low and not suitable for the need of the socialist market economy
and the rule of law principle.
</P>
<P>
"We must fight a lasting war to improve the work of the grass-
roots level procuratorates," he said.
</P>
<P>
He asked the related officials to improve the work in five
aspects: good leadership, good teamwork, good mechanism, good
performance and good image.
</P>
<P>
He also asked the party committees at all levels to instruct,
support and help the work of various procuratorates.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Luo Gan, who is also secretary of the Committee
of Political Science and Law Under the Chinese Communist Party (
CPC) Central Committee and a member of the Political Bureau of the
CPC Central Committee, also attended today's working meeting.
</P>
