<HEADLINE> Shanghai Orphanage Receives Car Donation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A reddish Ford Transit was
delivered to the Shanghai Orphanage today as a gift from the Ford
Motor China Ltd. and the British Chamber of Commerce in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The 12-seat luxury bus will be used for a Sino-British foster
care program for orphans in the welfare organization, according to
a local official.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai pioneered in 1997 to encourage families to offer their
care to children in orphanages. Under the program, 240 orphans now
live with ordinary Shanghai residents, with the cost of their
education and health care covered by orphanages.
</P>
<P>
"Care For Children," a British non-government charity, became
involved in the program in 1998, and since then, many British
families have extended their warm hands to Chinese orphans.
</P>
<P>
Li Yanlin, director of the Shanghai Social Welfare Center, said
that the family foster care of orphans has been popular in Western
countries. Shanghai has a lot to learn from foreign charitable
organizations on the matter.
</P>
<P>
The collective foster care of orphans in charitable
organizations is the principal way of taking care of the children
in China. 
