<HEADLINE> Int'l Workshop on Non-Timber-Made Paper Held in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth International
Workshop on Non-Timber-Made Paper was staged today in this capital
of east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 150 experts and entrepreneurs from more than 20 countries
and regions attended the four-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
China is the world's third largest paper producer. However, in
terms of non-timber-made, it is the largest. The Chinese
government has shut down some big polluters, which use non-timber
fibers to produce paper, as part of the efforts to control and
treat the pollution.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to boost the healthy development of
China's non-timber-made paper industry, said Huang Runbing,
general secretary of Chinese Academy of Paper Making.
</P>
<P>
He said that China hopes to introduce advanced environment
friendly paper-making technology.
</P>
<P>
The workshops is co-sponsored by the academy, the United
Nations Industrial Development Organization and TAPPI from the
United States.  
