Association of Nigeria and the National Union of Petroleum and
Natural Gas Workers went on strike after failing to reach an
agreement over their demand for a 25 percent payment increase with
the oil companies.
</P>
<P>
The workers vowed Sunday that they would continue with the
action until their demands would be met.
</P>
<P>
However, Obaseki said the NNPC had been in touch with the
management of oil companies and the striking workers with a view
to finding a last solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to the public not to resort to panic-buying as
the NNPC had sufficient stock of petroleum products to last the
nation several weeks.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, the biggest oil-producing country in Africa, depends
upon imported petroleum products for domestic consumption.
