<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drive-By Shooting Kills Three in Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A drive-by shooting from a
motorcycle killed three people Sunday night in the Dutch town of
Tilburg, police sources said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Carel Bouwmans told the press it seemed that
the attackers, a gunman and a motorcyclist, used automatic weapons
"because there were dozens of shots fired through the windows."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman declined to say whether the police had any clues
about the identities or the whereabouts of the attackers.
</P>
<P>
The drive-by shooting took place around midnight and killed a
couple, identified as Piet and Ria Verhagen, and the man's brother,
Jef Verhagen.
</P>
<P>
The police said that random killings are uncommon in the
Netherlands, despite a recorded increase of gang shootings in
recent years. 
</P>
