<HEADLINE> Xi'an Trade Fair Slated for October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Investment and Trade
Fair is scheduled to be held here October 3-8, and local officials
are working to make the annual event the largest since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Officials say the number of booths has increased to 700, 47
percent more than the previous fair and more than 4,000 domestic
and overseas business people have been invited.
</P>
<P>
Some 226 key investment projects in the fields of machinery,
electronics, agriculture, tourism and real estate will be
available for business talks.
</P>
<P>
A forum on project management and a seminar on opportunities
and challenges after China's entry into the World Trade
Organizations will be held during the fair. 
</P>
