<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetan Cultural Relics Be Shown in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region is
to put on show its exquisite cultural relics in an exhibition in
Shanghai, China's largest metropolis, in May 2001, a Tibetan
cultural relics official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibition will help local residents to have a better
understanding of Tibet, and it is sure to create quite a stir
among all walks of life in Shanghai," said Jin Yuwen, an official
of the Shanghai Municipal Cultural Heritage Management Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Museum has sent experts to Tibet to prepare for
the transportation of the exhibits, she said.
</P>
<P>
The three cities of Lhasa, Xigaze and Gyangze have been listed
by the state as famous historical sites in Tibet. Potala Palace, a
symbolic architecture which serves as the region's political and
religious center for centuries, has been included in the World
Heritage list. The exhibits will be chosen from the rich
collections there.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey on cultural relics in Tibet shows that the
region has 1,768 places of historical interests including cliff
painting, castles, palaces, temples and military ruins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Steps Up Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A provincial delegation set
out today to look into enforcement of environmental protection
laws in this island province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
It is a prelude to the province's "century tour" regarding
environmental protection for the year of 2000. The tour is
initiated by 14 local organizations including the environment and
resources working committee of Hainan Provincial People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consists of government officials and journalists.
Inspection into pollution treatment in industrial enterprises will
be the main task of the delegation which will also look into the
protection of wildlife and natural forests in the province, said
local sources.
</P>
<P>
During the 10-day inspection tour, the delegation will give
seminars on environmental protection laws and related information
about protecting the environment.
</P>
<P>
Out of Hainan's 167 major industrial enterprises, only 80 have
met pollution discharge standards through harnessing efforts, said
the sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
