<HEADLINE> CITIC Bank Offers Two Billion Loan to Shenzhen Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 18 (Xinhua)-- China International Trust and
Investment Industrial Bank (CITIC) provided two billion yuan in
loans (nearly 241 million U.S. dollars) today to two local
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Zhongxing Communication Ltd, Co., one of the loan
recipients, will use the loan as buyer's credit for its customers
while Shenzhen Expressway Ltd, Co., a company listed in Hong Kong,
will use the loan for infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1979, CITIC is a multinational group with assets
worth 189 billion yuan (22.7 billion U.S. dollars). The company
has a large variety of businesses ranging from banking and
securities to leasing. 
