<HEADLINE> Army to Host Int'l Medical Equipment Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition
on medical equipment, China Med 2001, will be held in Beijing
between April 18 and 22 next year, organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The People's Liberation Army (PLA) General Logistics Department,
China International Trade Center Co., Ltd. and China National
Medicines and Health Products Import and Export Corporation will
jointly sponsor the exhibition, the largest ever held in China.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said that nearly 400 medical equipment manufacturers
and dealers from China, the United States, Germany, Japan, Finland,
Switzerland, Sweden, Israel, Canada, Australia, Singapore, the
Netherlands, the Republic of Korea and France, as well as Hong
Kong and Taiwan will participate in the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits will include electronic apparatus, x-ray and
ultrasonic machines, optical equipment, biochemical test machines,
dental equipment and health care equipment, among others.
</P>
<P>
Yuan Tianxi, a senior officer with the Health Department under
the PLA General Logistics Department, said that the Chinese
military will purchase some medical equipment at the exhibition,
which will also serve as a forum for technological exchange,
especially in the field of high and new technology.
</P>
<P>
Yuan estimated that the trade volume at the exhibition may
reach 30 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 Chinese hospitals, medical institutes and
research institutes, including military establishments, will send
representatives to the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The developments of the show are also available on the website
of www.chinanet.net.cn.  
</P>
</TEXT>
