<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees Visits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) Sadako Ogata arrived in Iran on
Monday through the border city of Taibad in the northeastern
Khorasan Province, the official Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Ogata was welcomed at a border point by the head of the UNHCR
office in Iran and a number of Iranian officials.
</P>
<P>
Upon her arrival, Ogata boarded on a helicopter to inspect the
Mehman-Sharh camp in the province where Afghan refugees reside. She
is also to inspect several Afghan refugee camps in other parts of
Iran.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the U.N. official will review the repatriation
of Afghan refugees by Iran and discuss it with Iranian officials.
</P>
<P>
There are some 1.4 million Afghan refugees residing in Iran
according to official statistics, but independent estimates put the
number as high as 2 million.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR signed a plan with Iran in February on the repatriation of
Afghan refugees to their motherland. The plan was launched on April
8 and is to continue until October 11 this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 Afghan refugees have so far returned home
under the plan, the UNHCR office in Iran has announced.
</P>
<P>
Prior to her visit to Iran, Ogata paid visits to Pakistan and
Afghanistan and held talks with high-ranking Pakistani and Taliban
officials on the issue of Afghan refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
