<HEADLINE> Indian, Pak Troops Exchange Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- At least three civilians,
two Indians and one Pakistani, were injured when Indian Border
Security Forces and Pakistani rangers exchanged fire along the
International border in Kashmir Monday, official reports said.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of fire, which began Sunday evening with Pakistani
troops firing mortar shells on forward Indian posts in Poonch and
Palanwalla sectors, was still continuing, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
A shopkeeper was injured in the shelling in Abdullain village
in the R S Pura sector Monday afternoon while another person was
injured in the Pahapur border outpost of the Samba sector,
according to the Press Trust of India. 
