<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique: Agricultural and Livestock Census Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maputo, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The national agricultural and
livestock census, to be carried out by the Mozambican Agriculture
Ministry and the National Statistics Institute, was officially
launched in Maputo on Monday and is expected to be completed by
the end of November.
</P>
<P>
However, according to Monday's issue of the daily paper "
Noticias", preparations for the work, particularly staff training,
have been completed only in the southern region of the country.
Training is due to start in the central and northern regions in
the next few weeks.
</P>
<P>
In the central province of Manica, training is scheduled to
start before the end of September, whereas in the other central
and northern provinces it is planned for the first half of October.
</P>
<P>
The deputy director of the census, Domingos Diogo, said that
the 450 census staff will all have been trained by the end of
October.
</P>
<P>
The trainees will be organized into 77 brigades which will be
dispatched to the various provinces.
</P>
<P>
The enquiries will cover peasant family units, and medium and
large scale agricultural and livestock undertakings.
</P>
<P>
Diogo said that special attention is given to the training of
district agricultural directors since they are believed to be the
key to the mobilization of people and companies for this work, and
also because they must ensure the logistics for the brigades in
their respective areas.
</P>
<P>
This is the first agricultural census in the country since
independence in 1975, and is aimed at knowing the number of
agricultural and livestock units countrywide, their distribution
and productivity, and the main agricultural and farming activities
in each area, in order to facilitate the drafting of policies for
this sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
