<HEADLINE> Three Security Personnel Shot Dead in Indonesia's Aceh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Amid strong attempts to put
an end to the bloodshed in the riot-torn province of Indonesia's
Aceh, at least three security personnel were shot dead there on
Monday, Antara news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The three persons were shot by the Free Aceh Movement (GAM), an
underground armed Acehnese movement, who have been fighting for
the province's independence for more than 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Local security officer, Senior Superintendent Kusbini Imbar,
confirmed that the three security personnel were killed after
being involved in an exchange of fire in Pidie regency.
</P>
<P>
Aceh saw a series of terror actions in recent two weeks
following the extension of a cease fire agreement early September
between the GAM and the central government.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian President Abdurrahman Wahid has repeatedly called on
the Acehnese rebels to surrender and talk with the government. But
there is no signs that the calls will be met.
</P>
<P>
The central government issued a policy to implement the special
autonomy status bill to the province in a bid to calm down and
ease the independence's calls from the local people.
</P>
<P>
Under the status, the local authority will have a greater role
in determining policy of development. The province was also let to
implement the Islamic law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
