<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Indonesia's Bengkulu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A mild earthquake measuring 4.
0 on the Richter Scale rocked Indonesia's Bengkulu province on
Sunday night at about 19:42 p.m. (local time), a report reaching
here said Monday.
</P>
<P>
But no casualties or damages were reported.
</P>
<P>
Antara quoted an official of the local geophysics and
meteorology agency as saying that the epicenter of the quake was
located 1.99 south latitude and 101.37 east longitude, 33
kilometers beneath the sea.
</P>
<P>
On June 4, the province was also rocked by a powerful quake
measuring 7.8 on the Richter Scale which killed more than 120
people, injuring thousands.
</P>
<P>
The June's quake also destroyed thousands of buildings with an
estimated financial damage reached 400 billion rupiah (more than 7
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
