dollars or 62.7 percent more than Friday's total, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
After four consecutive days of modest decline, the market
failed to show any sign of life with a suddenly deteriorating mood.
Throughout the session, the index got clobbered and accelerated
its slide in the afternoon as investors turned nervous for lack of
crucial support.
</P>
<P>
Breadth figures were overwhelming negative with 54 declining
shares and not a single one on the rise.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predicted that there are no catalysts to drive
prices now and market players are impatient and would favor
selling, which may augur a hard time ahead. 
