<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior PLA Officer Holds Talks with Russian Guest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Wang Ke, head of the General
Logistics Department of the People's Liberation Army (PLA), held
talks here today with Vladimir Isakov, Russain vice minister of
defense and director of the logistics department of the Russian
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Wang, also a member of the Central Military Commission, said
that the Chinese and Russian people have enjoyed a long-term
friendship, adding that the leaders of the two countries have
exchanged views on the bilateral relations and major international
issues since the two countries built the strategic and cooperative
partnership.
</P>
<P>
He said that the military relations between China and Russia
have developed smoothly and the two sides have had frequent
exchange of visits. He noted that the cooperation between the two
armed forces in all fields has promoted Sino-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang briefed the guests on the reform of China's military
logistics system. He said that the visit of Isakov offers an
opportunity for cooperation between the two militaries in the
field of logistics, and Chinese PLA logistics department would
like have more cooperation with its Russian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
Isakov said that there are many similarities for Chinese and
Russian militaries in their logistics systems, and he believes
that this visit would further the cooperation between the two
armed forces in the logistics field.  
</P>
</TEXT>
