<HEADLINE> Singapore Shares Close 1.8 percent Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed 1.8
percent lower on Singapore Stock Market Monday on extended worries
over oil prices and weaker regional sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index was down 37.43 points to 2,
016.26.
</P>
<P>
Volume totaled 196.91 million units worth 490.19 million
Singapore dollars (283.35 million U.S. dollars). Decliners
overwhelmed advancers 289 to 60 with 220 stocks unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Chartered led the volume list with a turnover of 9.56 million
units. It was followed by ITech Grp which had 7.07 million shares
done. East Tech was the next with 7.04 million counters changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
Jar Mat, SIA 200 and UOB led the gainers list rising 10 cents
each to 4.86, 16.40 and 12.40 Singapore dollars respectively.
JurCem gained 6 cents to 1.76 Singapore dollars. Sp Bldg edged up
5 cents to 1.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 headed the descent of the day plunging 150 cents
to 37.50 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 sank 130 cents to 27.70
Singapore dollars. PacCent shed 120 cents to 20.20 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the market simply ignored the 27.3 percent
surge in non-oil domestic oil exports in August that was far
higher than expected. 
</P>
