<HEADLINE> IWF Allows Romanian Weightlifters to Compete in Sydney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYNDEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The International
Weightlifting Federation (IWF) said in a statement here on Monday
that the Romanian weightlifters can compete in the Olympic Games
since the Romanian side has agreed to pay a fine of 50, 000 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
"A discussion took place between the IWF and the Romanian NOC
on 18th September 2000, when Romania stated that they would pay
the fine and were asking the IWF to consent to the participation
of the other four weightlifters at these Games," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
"In accordance with its rules, the IWF Executive Board accepts
the request of the Romanian NOC," it said. "While of course
maintaining the suspensions imposed on the two lifters who tested
positive - it gives its consent to the participation of the
remaining four weightlifers in the Games."
</P>
<P>
But the IWF warned if the fine can not be paid to the IWF Anti-
Doping Fund by 17:00, on September 20th, 2000, the Romanian
Weightlifting Federation will be suspended immediately. The
athletes who have already lifted in the Games will be disqualified.
</P>
</TEXT>
