<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A Share Market Down at Monday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The turnover was 6.98 billion yuan, 4.12 percent less than last
Friday's 7.28 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Index opened higher at 613.53 points Monday morning, but
the selling pressure above 613 points led down the market. The
Index almost ended at the lowest level of 602.89 points.
</P>
<P>
High-tech shares were on the losers' list. The petrochemical
shares performed actively again, due to the high oil price.
</P>
<P>
Homeway predicted that the A-share market is likely to fall
Tuesday, and would test its low level of 600 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
