<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices fell in Tokyo
Monday in a market worried about declines on Wall Street, rising
oil prices and the plummeting euro.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 152.12 points, or 0.94
percent to close at 16,061.16.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, slid 2.55 points or 0.17 percent to 1,481.04.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 490.64 million
shares from last Thursday's 573.14 million shares. The Tokyo
market was closed last Friday for a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday's decline on Wall Street helped press down high-
tech issues, while many communications issues were also lower.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers exceeded
losers 677 to 599 despite falls in the Nikkei and TOPIX, with 132
issues remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
