<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Safin Tops ATP Rankings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Russia's U.S. Open champion
Marat Safin has gone top of the ATP standings at the age of just
20 following the publishing of the latest rankings in Monaco on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Safin, previously ranked third, climbed to the top following
his 6-3, 6-4 win over Italian Davide Sanguinetti in Sunday's
President's Cup final in Tashkent, Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
The Russian has 639 points, two points ahead of American Pete
Sampras, who lost the U.S. Open final at Flushing Meadow.
</P>
<P>
Safin has bagged five singles titles so far this year, in
Barcelona, Mallorca, Montreal, the U.S. Open and Tashkent.
</P>
<P>
In third place is Brazil's French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten,
who is competing in the Sydney Olympics, with 14 points to make up
on Sampras.
</P>
<P>
Fourth is former number one Magnus Norman of Sweden, with
Australian Lleyton Hewitt fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
