<HEADLINE> American Quann Wins Women's 100m Breaststroke Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- American Megan Quann outpaced
race leader Penny Heyns to take the women's 100m breaststroke
title at the Olympic Games here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Quann clocked in a winning time of 1:07.05 for the gold medal,
with the silver medal went to Leisel Jones of Australia in 1:07.49.
</P>
<P>
World record holder Heyns of South Africa, who led the first 80
meters, finished in third in 1:07.55. 
</P>
