<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- The Black Sea Partnership-2000, the concerted manoeuvres of
the Naval Forces Commandership, will start on Monday as the ships
arrive at the Istanbul harbour.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Naval Forces and Air Forces will send two frigates,
three assault boats, one submarine, one assistant ship and planes
respectively to take part in the five-day manoeuvres.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet:
</P>
<P>
-- A bomb planted by unidentified assailants beside an ATM
(Automatic Teller Machine) in Kagithane district of the Turkish
biggest city Istanbul exploded early on Sunday, causing financial
damage.
</P>
<P>
The police said efforts were underway to capture the assailants.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Gendarme Forces captured 47,717 illegal immigrants in
northwestern Edirne province in the last four years, among them 9,
952 people were captured in the first eight months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The illegal immigrants generally enter into Turkey from the
southeastern Anatolia Region and plan to illegally proceed to
Greece or Italy.
</P>
<P>
Yenibinyil:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish economists said that increasing gas prices could push
Turkey's inflation rate up considerably, thus jeopardizing the
government's anti-inflation program. 
