<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Three Insurers Announce Comprehensive Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Japan's three major insurers,
Tokio Marine and Fire Insurance Co., Asahi Mutual Life Insurance
Co. and Nichido Fire and Marine Insurance Co. announced Monday
that they plan to form a comprehensive tie-up with a view to
integrating their operations in the future.
</P>
<P>
"We agreed today to form a new insurance business group that
will merge our life and nonlife businesses," the three firms said
in a joint statement.
</P>
<P>
If formed, the three-way alliance would be Japan's largest
comprehensive insurance group, with combined assets of 19 trillion
yen (about 177.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Tokio Marine and Nichido are currently Japan's biggest and
seventh-largest nonlife insurers, respectively, while Asahi is the
fifth-biggest life insurer.
</P>
<P>
The tie-up arrangement came as competition in Japan's insurance
sector intensified following the Japanese government's decision to
give insurers the freedom to compete by offering lower premiums
and innovative policies.
</P>
<P>
The three insurers will immediately create a committee to craft
business strategies for cashing in on the merits springing from
the formation of the new alliance, they said.
</P>
<P>
The group strategy committee, to be headed by the presidents of
the three insurers, will have a range of subcommittees to devise
details of new business strategies for their various insurance
business fields.
</P>
<P>
The three said they will cooperate to develop new insurance
policies by combining the advantages of life and nonlife insurance
policies, while cooperating to build up new sales channels on the
strength of information technology.
</P>
<P>
The three insurers will also cooperate to offer attractive
products related to so-called "third-sector" insurance products,
such as cancer and medical insurance policies, which do not fall
into the two major conventional categories of life and casualty
insurance sectors, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0264 </DOCNO>
