<HEADLINE> Czech Woman Takes K1 Canoeing Olympic Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Stepanka Hilgertova of the
Czech Republic scored 247.04 points in the final two runs to take
the women's K1 canoeing-kayak gold medal at the Olympic Games here
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The silver and bronze medals went to two Frenchwomen as
Brigitte Guibal scored 251.88 and Anne-lise Bardet had 254.77
points.
</P>
<P>
On how she felt in the last minutes of the race knowing that
the French were so close behind, Hilgertova said that "I wasn't
really that worried because I knew that I had a chance at a medal.
I didn't know which one yet but I was very happy.
</P>
<P>
"I was worried about the weather but tried not to think about
it as the conditions are the same for everyone," said Hilgertova
who has now had two golds from the Olympics Games.
</P>
<P>
Elena Kasliska of Slovakia was fourth, followed by Irena
Pavelkova of the Czech Republic, Mandy Planert of Germany, Rebecca
Giddens of the United States and Australian Danielle Woodward.
</P>
