<HEADLINE> German Minister Hopes China to Join WTO Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 18 (Xinhua) -- German Economics and
Technology Minister Werner Muller stressed Monday it is important
for the current candidate for WTO membership -- China to join the
organization as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
As many countries as possible should be involved in the WTO
which continues to have the important task of pushing ahead with
the liberalization of world trade, he said at the opening of the
two-day 8th Asia-Pacific Convention of German Business here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the open world trade system is increasingly becoming a
buffer which can alleviate the impact of regional shocks on the
world economy.
</P>
<P>
"So it is vital that the talks in Geneva on implementing the
Uruguay Round results continue in a targeted fashion. In addition,
the efforts to get a new WTO Round going must be intensified," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the third ASEM summit is taking place in Seoul in
October, which ought to give a strong signal for a new WTO Round.
</P>
<P>
He said ASEM adds an inter-regional dimension to the
cooperation between European and Asian countries. 
