<HEADLINE> Americans Continue Run for Women's Softball Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Olympic debutante Crystl
Bustos is just one home run away from equalling the Olympic home
run record after spearheading the United States to a 3-0 win over
Cuba at the Olympic Games softball competition here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Bustos smashed Cuba pitcher Laritza Espinosa for home runs over
center and right fields at her first two plate appearances to
bring her Olympic homer total to three after just two days of the
competition.
</P>
<P>
With another five preliminary games and finals to be played,
the short stop is widely tipped to smash the Olympic tournament
record of four set by Japan's Haruka Saito.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by Bustos, veteran Sheila Douty also homered over the
left field fence for the Americans' only other score.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dominated play with big hitting but was uninspiring in
the field with three errors, including two wild throws to first
base by starting pitcher Danielle Henderson.
</P>
<P>
Olympic newcomers Cuba struggled with the bat with only two
players, Diamela Puente and Haydee Hernandez, mananing hits.
However, the Cubans played a strong defensive game to hold the
Americans to three runs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
