<HEADLINE> Australian Naval Ship Deployed for Solomons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- An Australian naval ship has
been deployed for the Solomon Islands from Sydney Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
According to a media release, Minister for Defense John Moore
said that the ship "will provide a stabilizing presence and help
further promote the peace process in the Solomons".
</P>
<P>
Since the armed clashes broke out in the Solomon Islands,
Australia has been involved as a mediator and two naval ships were
deployed in succession in the island country in June and July,
providing a neutral venue for negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The minister said "the Australian government wishes to
encourage the Solomon Islands parties to resolve their substantive
issues in a peaceful, cooperative manner, and in accordance with
the Solomon Islands Constitution."
