<HEADLINE> Australia Proclaims a "Roadstead" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Australia proclaimed a "
roadstead" in waters off north Queensland Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Associated Press quoted Attorney-General Daryl
Williams as saying that the proclamation extended the existing
limits of Australia's territorial sea in the form of a roadstead
near the Queensland port of Karumba, in the south of the Gulf of
Carpentaria.
</P>
<P>
There is no report on the size of the roadstead.
</P>
<P>
According to Williams, it was the first roadstead declared in
Australia and allowed the government to exercise sovereignty over
the waters contained within the roadstead. 
</P>
