<HEADLINE> Lithuanian Wins Women's Shooting Trap Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Lithuania's Daina
Gudzineviciute scored 93 hits to get the women's shooting trap
title at the Olympic Games here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I feel wonderful, it still is difficult to believe I won, but
it will come to me," said Gudzineviciute, who won the second gold
medal for Lithuania at the Games.
</P>
<P>
"It is a good feeling. A lot of people have come to know (
Lithuania) through the basketball, now people connected to this
sport will now think of Lithuania."
</P>
<P>
"I didn't realise that if I missed the last shot I would have
an additional shot," said the Lithuanian woman, who beat Delphine
Racinet of France by one shit, "I wasn't counting else's misses.
The calculator in your mind is always working, the thing I was
thinking was I can't have any more misses."
</P>
<P>
On her opposition, she said "there have been many strong
shooters, they were all strong shooters."
</P>
<P>
"I'm a Lithuanian, I live in the capital, I am shooting for a
very long time, there were good times and there were bad times,
but shooting represents a major part of my life."
</P>
<P>
On shooting at the Sydney International Shooting Center, she
said that "I would probably say that this range is one of the more
difficult ones. For example in Italy, it is very different there
and you can't compare, you tend to get an optical illusion here."
</P>
<P>
Racinet finished second with 92 hits and China's Gao E took the
bronze medal with 90 hits. 
