<HEADLINE> 8th Asia-Pacific Conference of German Business Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The 8th Asia-Pacific
Convention of German Business opened here Monday to serve as a
platform for German and Asian organizations to form smart
partnership.
</P>
<P>
The two-day convention themed "New dynamics in the Asia-Pacific
Region: Innovation-Technology-Cooperation" aims to improve
economic conditions and to encourage a greater commitment of
German organizations in the Asia-Pacific region, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The convention will discuss up-to-date topics concerning the
Asian region being of crucial interest to German organizations of
all industries doing business with Asian counterparts, they said.
</P>
<P>
Participants will deliberate on E-commerce in Asia, legal
protection in partner countries in Asia, the framework change for
financing in Asia, marketing and distribution of German
technologies in Asia, and education cooperation between Germany
and Asia at workshops during the convention.
</P>
<P>
There will be a number of workshops on individual economies in
the region including China, Hong Kong, Chinese Taipei, Australia,
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), India, Indonesia,
Japan, Malaysia, Philippines, Singapore, South Korea, Thailand and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Business matchings are scheduled between German delegates and
other organizations in the Asian market to discuss financial
support, technical cooperation, technology transfer, joint
ventures, and direct investment and trade business.
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with the convention, an exhibition is also being
organized with financial institutions, government agencies, small
and medium industries and professional organizations showcasing
their projects, technology, products and services to the
participants.
</P>
<P>
Over 500 business delegates from Germany and this region are
taking part in the convention initiated by the German Asia Pacific
Economic Committee and organized by the Malaysian-German Chamber
of Commerce and Industry.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Pacific Convention of German Business is held
biannually since 1986 in selected Asian key partner countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
The last one was held in Beijing, China, in 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
