<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Retake Northern Key Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
had recaptured the town of Chavakachcheri, the second largest one
in the northern Jaffna peninsula, from separatist rebels of
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), the army chief was quoted
as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Army Commander Lt. General Lionel Balagalle told The Island
newspaper that the troops had been able to capture the town within
four hours of fierce fighting after the launch of the operation on
Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
He said the operation was a combined security forces operation
aimed at weakening the LTTE rebels and retaking areas lost to
rebels during March to May this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the LTTE rebels said in a statement Sunday night that
government troops had entered the outskirts of Chavakachcheri town
and heavy fighting was raging.
</P>
<P>
Chavakachcheri, the main town between Elephant Pass and Jaffna
on the 53 kilometer main supply route, was captured by the LTTE
rebels in April this year shortly after the fall of the strategic
Elephant Pass.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels are fighting a 17-year war against majority
Sinhalese dominated government in a bid to carve out a separate
state for minority Tamils in the country's north and east. More
than 60,000 people have been killed in the ethnic war.
</P>
<P>
Balagalle said the rebels had suffered heavy losses with four
soldiers being killed and 46 others injured. He said air and
artillery strikes including the use of Multi Barrel Rocket
Launchers had successfully destroyed the rebels' mortar positions.
</P>
<P>
He claimed that the military was strengthening its position in
the peninsula and added that this month alone over 400 LTTE rebels
had been killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
