<HEADLINE> Thai Exports to New Markets Grow Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports to the
markets considered new to the country, such as China, Mongolia,
Latin America and South Asia, are growing at a fast pace, the
Commerce Ministry said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
A report from the ministry said that in July, on a year-on-year
basis, exports to China and Mongolia increased by about 55 percent,
Latin America by 49.4 percent, followed by South Asia, which grew
by about 45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Without disclosing the figures of export value to those markets,
it said that "the growth of export value to these new markets have
been satisfactory."
</P>
<P>
To boost exports to the new markets, the commerce ministry have
also provided funds of about 46 million baht (1.1 million U.S.
dollars) to private export operators dealing with these markets,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The robust export growth, which increased 27 percent in the
first eight months this year, has become the main engine for the
country's economic recovery. To sustain the growth, Thailand is
exploring new markets around the world besides its traditional
markets such as North America, Europe, and Japan. 
