<HEADLINE> Picture Album of Former Chinese Leaders Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A picture album of late
leaders of the People's Republic of China, including Mao Zedong,
Zhou Enlai and Deng Xiaoping, was launched here today, according
to the "People's Daily", China's leading national newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The album, titled "Leaders of the Republic", contains about 170
pictures, including pictures of Mao Zedong, Zhou Enlai, Liu Shaoqi,
Zhu De, Ren Bishi, Deng Xiaoping and Chen Yun.
</P>
<P>
The pictures were taken during different periods of their
revolutionary careers, vividly displaying their struggle for the
founding of the new China, and the zigzag road to an independent,
reunified, democratic, prosperious and powerful China..
</P>
<P>
The publication was compiled by the Literature Research Center
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
and published by the Literature Publishing House of the CPC
Central Committee. 
