<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Myanmar Int'l Airport Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A new Myanmar airport of world
class, the Mandalay International Airport in the northern city of
Mandalay, was put into service Sunday, becoming another gateway
linking Myanmar with foreign countries after the Yangon
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The Mandalay International Airport, located in Tada U township,
28.8 kilometers southwest of Mandalay which is also the second
largest city of Myanmar, was built at a cost of 150 million U.S.
dollars plus 6.496 billion Kyats (18.56 million dollars) under a
contract with the Italian-Thai Development Public Co Ltd of
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council General Maung Aye inaugurated the airport with airliner of
the Thai Airways International, the first foreign airliner,
touching down the airport, official newspaper The New Light of
Myanmar reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The area of the airport is 10,131 hectares and its runway is
one of the longest in Southeast Asia with a length of 4,200 meters
and a width of 60 meters.
</P>
<P>
The airport has six passenger boarding bridges and three of
them can handle modern Boeing 747-400 planes.
</P>
<P>
The airport, which has a four-storey terminal, will be able to
handle 8,000 passengers a day and three million passengers a year.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the airport started in March 1994.
</P>
<P>
There are 66 airports in Myanmar now with 26 international air
routes passing through the air territory of Myanmar and planes
from domestic airlines fly in the air territory about 10,000 times
and those from international airlines about 60,000 times every
year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
