<HEADLINE> McCoy Wins Valencia 500cc GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Garry McCoy won
the Valencia 500cc Grand Prix on Sunday in Valencia, Spain, while
American Kenny Roberts came second to close in on his first world
championship title.
</P>
<P>
Taking the lead on the fifth lap, McCoy of the Yamaha team held
it all the way to the finish line.
</P>
<P>
Roberts of the Suzuki team rode a controlled race to finish
just over five seconds behind. But Roberts has won four of his
last five races.
</P>
<P>
McCoy covered the 30 laps of the Cheste circuit in 48 minuets
27.799 seconds to became the first rider to score successive wins
in the 500cc category in 23 races.
</P>
<P>
Roberts collected 20 points for second place which gave him 214
points at the top of the standings. He now leads his nearest
rival, Italy's Honda rider Valentino Rossi, by 66 points.
</P>
<P>
Rossi, in his first year in the blue riband catagory, however
still has a chence to overtake the lead as there are three races
remaining.
</P>
<P>
Rossi crashed four laps before the finish while in second place
when he chased leading McCoy too hard in search of the race lead
and lost control.
</P>
<P>
Roberts said he go back home and relax to prepare for the
Brazilian Grand Prix in Rio de Jeneiro on October 7. He aims to
give Suzuki their first 500cc world title since Kevin Schwantz's
in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
