<HEADLINE> 9 Olympians Suspended for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of nine Olympians have
been suspended for taking banned drugs, including six who have
been banned from the athletes' village, International Olympic
Committee officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
IOC Medical Commission chief Patrick Schamash said the other
three - all wrestlers, two from Egypt and one from Morocco - were
suspended before they arrived at the village.
</P>
<P>
The six athletes kicked out of the village were a weightlifter
from Chinese Taipei, an Iranian boxer, a swimmer from Kazakstan, a
weightlifter from Norway and two weightlifters from Romania, he
said.
</P>
<P>
All were the result of out-of-competition tests.
</P>
<P>
Schamash did not identify the drugs or athletes involved.
</P>
