<HEADLINE> Russian Heads Qualifiers for Women's 200m Individual Medley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Oksana Verevka had a
solid swim in the heats of the Sydney Olympic women's 200m
individual medley on Monday morning and was the fastest qualifier
for the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Swimming in heat three, Verevka overtook race leader Tomoko
Hagiwara of Japan in the final 50m and finished in 2:13.48.
Hagiwara was second in 2:15.16
</P>
<P>
Verevka could spoil Ukrainian Yana Klochkova's chances of
adding to her gold in the 400m individual medley.
</P>
<P>
Klochkova, in heat five, established a lead in the backstroke
leg but in the second half of the race, she was challenged by
American Cristian Teuscher and the two went stroke heading into
the wall.
</P>
<P>
Klochkova touched just ahead in 2:13.83, the third fastest time
of the morning while Teuscher clocked 2:14.17 to be the fifth
fastest qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Bronze medalist from the 400m individual medley, Romania's
Beatrice Caslaru, and Canada's Joanne Malar looked in form in
their heat. Caslaru won in 2:13.72 with Malar second in 2:13.92.
</P>
