<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Rowers on Track for Gold in Women's Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian women's eight
produced one of the most dominating performances of the day in the
first heat at the Syndey Olympic rowing regatta on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian eight, undefeated since winning the gold medal at
the Atlanta Olympics, started faster than their competition and
led the field by 4.8 seconds at the half-way mark. Romania pushed
on in the final 1,000 meters and eventually won by more than 10
seconds with Australia in second place just ahead of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
The second heat was won by the Netherlands, who came from
behind to beat Canada and early leaders the United States.
</P>
<P>
Romania and the Netherlands progress straight to the final on
Sunday with the rest of the field to row in an elimination
repechage on Wednesday. 
</P>
