<HEADLINE> Croatia, Australia Through to Finals of Men's Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Current world champion the
United States was beaten by Croatia in the men's eight first heat
at the Sydney International Regatta Center on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Croatians made a good start and had a lead of 0.42 second
at the 500m mark, which they built on gradually on throughout the
race, eventually finishing 2.37 seconds in front of the Americans.
</P>
<P>
Australia then upset this year's World Cup winner Britain in
the second heat after leading from start to finish. Australia set
the fastest time for every 500m section of the race and crossed
the finish line 1.62 seconds ahead.
</P>
<P>
While Australia was out in front, Canada and Britain battled
for second place. It was the Britons who pulled ahead at the 1,
000m mark and gradually moved away from their rivals.
</P>
<P>
Croatia and Australia won straight through to the final on
Sunday, while all remaining crews get another chance in the
repechage on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
