<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Athlete Baumann Banned for Two Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Dieter Baumann of Germany was
banned for two years Monday after the International Amateur
Athletics Federation (IAAF) rejected an appeal against a positive
dope test, the IAAF announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The track and field world governing body announced the ban
after a two-day arbitration hearing between the IAAF and the
German Athletics Federation.
</P>
<P>
Baumann, the 1992 Olympic gold medallist in the 5,000 meters,
tested positive for the banned steroid nandrolone twice in October
and November 1999.
</P>
<P>
Baumann made a brief visit to Sydney on Friday, but did not
appear at the hearing before returning to Queensland, where
Germany has its Olympic training camp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
