<HEADLINE> UN Chief Supports East Timor Boxer in Participating at Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Secretary-
General Kofi Annan sent a personal letter to one of the first East
Timorese athletes to participate at the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The letter of support will be delivered to lightweight boxer
Victor Ramos Monday by Iqbal Riza, Secretary-General Kofi Annan's
Chef de Cabinet and representative at the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the United Nations successfully appealed to
the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to allow the East
Timorese to take part in the Games, the UN Information Center said.
The four-member team marched in the opening ceremony as individual
athletes behind an Olympic flag.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Mr Riza will present the East Timorese boxer with
the letter at a press conference at the Olympic Village to be
attended by IOC vice-president Kevan Gosper, and Olympic Aid
chairman Johann Koss. 
</P>
</TEXT>
