<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dutch Woman Favorite for Cycling Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Dutch woman Leontien van
Moorsel-Zijlaard will be the host favorite when she takes on
Marion Clignet of France in Monday's final of the women's
individual pursuit, following her successive Olympic and world
record setting rides in the preliminary phases of event on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal race will be between Sarah Ulmer of New
Zealand and Yvonne McGregor of Britain.
</P>
<P>
The longest day of the track cycling progarm will also feature
the qualifying rounds of the men's and women's sprint, followed by
the qualifying rounds of the men's 4,000 meters teams pursuit.
</P>
<P>
Of the 11 events contested on Monday, the only medal event will
be the finals of the women's 3,000m individual pursuit.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary rounds of the men's and women's sprint take
competition through to the quarterfinal round. The teams pursuit
will go through to the semifinal round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0387 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba and United States Expected to Continue Winning Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and the United States are
expected to continue their winning streak at the Sydney Olympics
at the baseball center Monday when they play Italy and South
Africa respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Cubans are coming off a resounding 16-0 victory over South
Africa and will be determined to extend their 19-game winning
streak in Olympic baseball.
</P>
<P>
With every starting player collecting a hit Sunday, the Cubans
are on fire with the bat, and their pitching staff did not give up
a hit.
</P>
<P>
Italy will struggle for hits against Cuba, but are stronger
opposition than South Africa and will be more competitive. The
game should go the full nine innings, but Cuba should win easily.
</P>
<P>
The American team are on a high after their exciting 13 innings
victory over Japan Sunday. Mike Neill showcased the Americans
power with his game-breaking home run to lead his country to
victory.
</P>
<P>
South Africa shouwed they were out of their league with the 16-
0 loss to Cuba and can't expect any respite against the American
team. The South Africans will improve after their first Olympic
baseball experience, but it will not show against the Americans.
</P>
</TEXT>
