<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2020 GMT, September 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- It is still not clear whether Israel could reach a
peace agreement with the Palestinians during the coming several
months, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak told his cabinet on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
There have been neither positive responses nor signals from the
Palestinian side and it is still uncertain whether the Israeli-
Palestinian peace talks could be moved forward or the two sides
could strike a deal in a very short period of time, Barak said.
</P>
<P>
However, Barak did not say what measures he will take to push
the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks forward. (Israel-Barak-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Resisting the United States both politically and
militarily over the past 10 years, Iraq is now trying to show its
defiance over the U.S. domination in the world economy.
</P>
<P>
At present, a group of financial experts, appointed by the Iraqi
government, are studying the possibility of replacing the U.S.
dollar with another "politically correct" currency as termed by the
Iraqi officials.
</P>
<P>
Their study will mainly focus on the euro, officially launched
on January 1, 1999 by the European Union (EU) as a counter-balance
to the U.S. dollar in the world financial market as well as in the
world economy. (Iraq-US-Dollar)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwait said Monday that it welcomes a neutral
body to inspect the oil field near the Kuwaiti-Iraqi borders, where
Iraq has accused Kuwait of stealing Iraqi oil.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Oil Minister Sheikh Saud Nasser Al-Sabah, in remarks to
the official Kuwait News Agency, said that all drilling and
production works conducted by the Kuwait Oil Company have been in
the Kuwaiti side.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saud said the company is "using conventional methods in
the oil drilling operations, which go in harmony with its oil
stockpiles." (Kuwait-Iraq-Oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's Foreign Ministry on Monday rejected Iraqi
allegations that Iran had involved in the rocket attack in Baghdad
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Iran has no links with such activities and Tehran has nothing
to do with Iraq's internal conflicts," an unnamed Foreign Ministry
official said, quoted by the official IRNA news agency.
</P>
<P>
Three 122 mm rockets exploded at residential districts in
Baghdad Sunday morning, injuring one person and destroying several
houses. (Iran-Iraq-Denial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinians are consulting Egypt and Jordan on the
demarcation of the borders with the two Arab neighbors, in an
effort to facilitate the return of their territories occupied by
Israel.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Zakaria Al-Agha, member of the executive
department of Fatah movement, the mainstay of the Palestine
Liberation Organization (PLO), here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The consultations were aimed at underscoring the necessity of
returning territories occupied by Israel since the 1967 war to
Palestinian sovereignty, he noted. (Palestine-Egypt-Jordan)
</P>
</TEXT>
