<HEADLINE> Venezuela, U.S. Discuss Accords on Venezuelan Oil Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The meetings between officials of the two countries were held
in Washington and New York, the president of the state-owned
Petroleos de Venezuela (PDVSA), Hector Ciavaldini, told the press.
</P>
<P>
Ciavaldini traveled around the United States, where he
inspected different oil investment and development areas.
</P>
<P>
PDVSA and U.S. Energy Department officials will examine their
energy cooperation issues at Washington on September 21, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ciavaldini said he informed people of the U.S. Congress and the
Energy Department on the position of the Venezuelan government,
which is in favor of fair prices for oil producers and consumers.
</P>
<P>
The official underlined the increase in Venezuela's oil-
production capability through investments and said it is
forecasted that by the end of the year, the country's oil
production will reach 3.95 million oil-barrels per day. 
</P>
