<DOCNO> XIE20000918.0395 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe's Leading Stock Markets Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- European stocks fell across
the board Monday on profit taking from technology issues amid
nervousness about the outlook for earnings, inflation and interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE-100 index fell 7.1 points, or 0.1 percent, to 6,
410.2 points, its lowest close since August 11.
</P>
<P>
High-tech firms suffered the most as Nasdaq's recent declines
produced a hangover. Internet security provider BLM shed 6.3
percent, computer chip designer ARM fell 3.2 percent and telecom
operator CW tumbled 8.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Oil companies got a boost from the strength of the price of
crude. BP Amoco rose 2.7 percent while Shell Transport &AMP; Trading
gained 2.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The broader FTSE Eurotop 300 index fell 0.5 percent. Its
computer services segment shed 3.1 percent while the electrical
and electronics sub-index was down 2.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's Xetra Dax index was down 1.1 percent at 6,921.22,
with airline Deutsche Lufthansa among the leading losers.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 index dropped 1.4 percent to 6,522.38, led
by telephone equipment maker Alcatel with a slide of 4.5 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
